 Sam Querrey  in the first rubber of the semi-finals of the Davis
Cup to give Spain a 1-0 lead.  U.S. Open semifinalist Ferrer beat the 22nd-ranked
American, 4-6, 6-2, 6-2, 6-4, on home soil  in Gijon.  Argentina and the Czech Republic are contesting the other
semifinal, which will get under way later today in Buenos Aires.  The U.S. last won the menâ€™s team elite competition in
